content.description: Climb up a to a big under cling with a horn on top. Surmount the roof and continue through the thinner and thinner holds to the top.
content.location: Starts in the middle of the southeast face, at the left end of a platform created by a fallen tree.

content.description: Start in the corner at the left end of the sloping ledge then stay on the right wall. The route heading left in the corner is Broken Arrow.
content.protection:
On the upper part of the South Face, facing the road. Can be reached by climbing Paper Clip.

The route starts in the corner on the left end of the sloping ledge. It is the right of the two bolt lines starting there.
content.location: Bolts to bolted anchor with rap rings

content.description: Start on nice, easy features. Crux is about two thirds the way up where the holds get thin. Well-protected the whole way up. There is a variation finish moving right at the top and keeping the overall grade in the 5.10 range.
content.protection: 12 bolts plus two bolt anchor. Bring 14 draws unless you plan on skipping bolts. You'll need a 60 meter rope.
content.location: 3 routes left of "Fleet Feet of Summer", starting in the chimney after a short easier route (10a?) just right of Yosemite Sam's, then moving right

content.description: Follow the line of bolts near the Arete.
content.location: Can be accessed by traversing right (past several anchors) from the top of Paper Clip. The start of the route is at the top anchor of "Enigma de la Gauche" or "The chocolate box arete

content.description:
Left most route on the bottom part of the south face. From the storm drain scramble up to a tree. The route starts at the far left behind the tree.

This route provides easy access to the routes higher up on the South Face.
content.location: On the right side of the south face (facing the road), right above the large storm drain.

content.description: Follow the right most line of bolts from the sloping ledge. At the top trend left towards the anchor.
content.protection: Bolts, bolted anchor with rap rings
content.location: Climbs up the right most line of bolts on the sloping ledge on the South Face (facing the road). Can be reached by climbing Paper Clip and continues almost straight above this climb.

content.description: Second route from the left on the bottom part of the south face. Starts at a shoulder height bolt. The second bolt can easily be reached from a very short "ramp" slightly to the left.
content.location: On the right side of the south face (facing the road), right above the large storm drain.

content.description: More sustained than The Connection (immediate to the left). Well bolted at the crux.
content.protection: Bolts, bolted anchors with rap rings at the top.
content.location: Second route from the right on the sloping ledge n the South Face (facing the road). Can be reached by climbing Paper Clip.

content.description: On the right hand side of the South Face, already facing somewhat away from the road. From a is back start follows the left side of the arÃªte. Crux is at the 4th bolt and a section of thin face with few, small feet.
content.location: 6th route from the left, 5th route from the right on the lower part of the face.

content.description: From the belay middle anchor on the sloping ledge climb straight up.
content.protection: Bolts, bolted anchor with rap rings.
content.location:
Third route from the right on the sloping ledge on the South Face (facing the road).

Can be reached by climbing Paper Clip.

content.description: Climb the corner and partially left wall, then at the top trend right towards the anchor shared with Uncle Tom's Short Story.
content.protection: Bolts to bolted anchor with rap rings
content.location:
On the upper part of the South Face, facing the road. Can be reached by climbing Paper Clip.

The route starts in the corner on the left end of the sloping ledge. It is the left of the two bolt lines starting there.
